***Those numbers given in the original post are WAY off form the uberest of paladin profiles I have ever seen ***<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=364397">www.magelo.com/eq_view_pr...num=364397</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Hope this link works. I am no Paladin, so I am sure they may be some pieces that have better upgrades. My main focus when I did this Magelo was to focus on hitpoints with a little utility in FT items, all Armor Class was just a bonus. Unfortanetly Magelo wont display the proper AC and the AC should be 2095 not 1095, not sure why Magelo does this. The best warrior I made has 6136 hp and AC of 1700ish, though AC was never a concern once again as HP was the focus. Before anyone says a Paladin will never see these item, remember this is the best vs the best, and in a DKP system it would be easy for a Paladin to this vs a Warrior as points are based on attendance.<br>
<br>
Its true many of the spells I listed under a Paladin become extinct in a raid but in a pinch they are there if needed. You will never hear &quot; All the Clerics are dead, buy the warrior time to camp so he can ress a Cleric &quot;. In very fast xp groups, you will generally go for a damage dealer over a Cleric but healing is still needed, Paladins do nicely here as they not only bring buffs but they bring a vast assortement of utility spells.<br>
<br>
As to DPS one handed, I agree, Paladins lack the DPS they should be doing from their holy blades BUT even with the weapon I used in the Magelo they can hold agro over a Warrior using EB weapon + Primal. Haven't tested vs dbl EB weapons and the reason they can hold agro is procs are luck while a spell cast is at will. As a warrior I would gladly give up DPS to hold agro with a spell or key that can generate agro at the push of a button, sadly the taunt key doesnt due this.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
As to what the answer is? Well items when made to all / all with 100 to 125 hp + stats + AC + saves it destroyed where the warrior sat in hitpoints and with AC capped at 1200ish then AC no longer matters. I personally dont care about hitpoints at this point unless they gave a skill to put warriors a few thousand above everyone else, but this isnt going to happen. The best bet, would be to remove the skill Defensive as a discipline and let it be a natural full time skill for the warrior and have it so it doesnt decrease their DPS as it does the mob. Sure this would be powerful but would secure their roll from all other classes as no other can mitigate as good as that. The other option is to make the discipline Defensive have no time limit, thus once entered you stay that way till dead or till you leave the defensive stance. AA skills I wont touch here but they need alot of retuning and new ones added for warriors ( not saying some other classes dont need work as well ).<br>
<br>
Sorry I don't have more time to respond, on break for lunch atm from work. <br>
<br>
